#: ../../content/guides/tips/parallel-builds.md:1
msgid "Parallel builds"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/guides/tips/parallel-builds.md:3
msgid ""
"A stage for a package (such as a build stage) can take advantage of "
"multiple cores to perform the step. By default, releng-tool will attempt "
"to run as many jobs for a stage equal to the amount of physical cores on "
"the host system. The amount of jobs available for a stage can be "
"configured using the [`--jobs`](arg-jobs) argument. For example, if a "
"user wishes to override the amount of jobs attempted for stages to two "
"jobs, the following can be used:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/guides/tips/parallel-builds.md:14
msgid ""
"If the total number of jobs provided is negative, it will subtract the "
"provided value from the automatic job detection count (to a minimum of "
"one). For example, to use one less job than normally used:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/guides/tips/parallel-builds.md:22
msgid ""
"Note that a developer may adjust the amount of jobs allowed for a "
"specific package if a package cannot support parallel processing using "
"the [`LIBFOO_FIXED_JOBS`](pkg-opt-fixed-jobs) or [`LIBFOO_MAX_JOBS`](pkg-"
"opt-max-jobs) package options."
msgstr ""

